New Chelsea owner, Todd Boehly, is ready to accept Inter Milan’s offer to take Romelu Lukaku on loan. This was confirmed by respected Italian transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano. According to him, the final loan fee will be €8m plus add-ons. Romano tweeted: Inter and Chelsea are now preparing paperworks to sign and complete the negotiation for Romelu Lukaku. “Todd Boehly, prepared to accept final loan fee worth €8m plus add-ons. “Thomas Tuchel wanted Lukaku to leave the club as the Belgian striker was only pushing for Inter.” Lukaku is set to return to the San Siro, only one year after he left for Stamford Bridge in a €100m transfer.